<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, October 30 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM -- At least 60 people were killed and 190 injured
when a fire broke out in a disco in the western Swedish city of
Gothenburg Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
The blaze started about midnight when about 400 young people,
aged from 13 to 20, gathered for a Halloween party on the second
floor of the local Macedonian Association building. Most of those
present were immigrants from Macedonia or Somalia.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the fire is still unknown, but the police have not
ruled out arson. (Sweden-Fire-Toll)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Palestinian security forces raided the house of
spiritual leader of the Islamic militant group Hamas Sheikh Ahmed
Yassin in Gaza Thursday night searching for a Palestinian
fugitive, Israel Radio reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The telephone line in Yassin's house was also cut off, the
radio said.
</P>
<P>
Yassin was not allowed out for prayer Friday since he was under
a house arrest placed by Palestinian National Authority (PNA)
Thursday, according to local radio and TV reports.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian officials said Yassin was confined to house arrest
"because his recent statements were against the Palestinian
national interests."
</P>
<P>
The unprecedented move, the first the PNA has taken against the
Hamas leader since he returned to Gaza in October 1997, was seen
as part of PNA's efforts to round up Hamas activists in the wake
of a suicide bombing Thursday in Gaza.
</P>
<P>
An Israeli soldier was killed when a Palestinian car loaded
with explosives rammed into an Israeli military jeep escorting a
bus carrying about 40 children of settlers and blew up outside the
major Jewish settlement of Gush Katif. (Palestinians-Yassin-Raid)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- A senior official of the Afghan Taliban has
admitted secret contacts between Iran and the militia, and
disclosed that some top Taliban officials had paid secret visits
to Iran in the past.
</P>
<P>
Abdul Hakim Muneeb disclosed that the Taliban had in the past
sent a high-ranking delegation to Iran. However, talks with Iran
could not yield any results, according to a report Friday by the
News Network International (NNI).
</P>
<P>
NNI quoted Muneeb as saying in an interview that as a result of
secret contacts with the Iranian officials, the delegation was
sent to Tehran to persuade the Iranians to end interference in
Afghanistan's internal affairs. (Afghanistan-Taliban-Iran)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin left here Friday for
the Black Sea resort of Sochi on a vacation prescribed by his
doctors to recuperate from "serious fatigue."
</P>
<P>
Before departure, Yeltsin met with Prime Minister Yevgeny
Primakov at the Vnukovo-2 airport on Primakov's trip to Austria
and his meeting with Aslan Maskhadov, president of the Russian
republic of Chechnya.
</P>
<P>
The 67-year-old president was scheduled to go to Vienna Tuesday
to attend the Russia-EU summit, but the trip was cancelled at the
last minute when his doctors advised him to stay put and take a
vacation. (Russia-Yeltsin-Vacation) 
</P>
</TEXT>
