<HEADLINE> Unemployment Drops in France to Record Low Since 1995 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 30 (Xinhua) -- Unemployment rate in France
dropped to 11.7 percent by the end of September, the record low
since October 1995, said the government on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The number of jobless people dropped by 42,900, or 1.4 percent,
as compared with the end of August, and stood at 2,954,700.
</P>
<P>
The number of jobless people under the age of 25 dropped by 3.5
percent in September, while that of unemployed people aged between
25 and 49 dropped by 1.2 percent and that of chronically
unemployed people dropped by 1 percent.
</P>
<P>
The number of unemployed people above 50 increased by 4.3
percent as compared with the same month last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
