<HEADLINE> Simitis: Government Would Strive for Three Major Targets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, October 30 (Xinhua) -- The Greek government would be
striving to attain three major targets during the coming period,
Greek Prime Minister Costas Simitis said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the new cabinet after a mini reshuffle, Simitis said
that the first target was to maintain and increase the pace of the
upward and developmental course of the Greek economy, the ultimate
objective being the country's entry to the European Economic and
Monetary Union (EMU).
</P>
<P>
The second was to strengthen Greece's role on the international
scene while the third was to improve the quality of life and deal
with Greek citizens' daily problems, particularly unemployment,
crime and issues concerning the country's health services, the
premier said.
</P>
<P>
As for the cabinet reshuffle last night, Simitis stressed that
this means the continuation of his government's task but at a more
intensive pace, with greater attention to problems, speed and
efficiency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
