<HEADLINE> French Judicial Authorities Open File Against Pinochet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 30 (Xinhua) -- The French judicial authorities
Friday opened a file against former Chilean president Augusto
Pinochet at the request of three families whose members were
killed or arrested and disappeared in Chile during the
dictatorship of Pinochet from 1973 to 1990.
</P>
<P>
Agence France-Presse quoted official sources as saying that the
Paris Public Prosecutor's Office has yet to designate a judge to
be in charge of the file.
</P>
<P>
The move came after the lawyer of three French families,
William Bourdon, sent a memorandum to Paris prosecutor Jean-Pierre
Dintilhac on Monday, calling on the French government to demand
extradition of Pinochet from Britain.
</P>
<P>
Pinochet was restored a half status of liberty on Friday by the
London High Court but remained under police surveillance.
</P>
</TEXT>
