<HEADLINE> OAU Ministerial Meeting on Refugees to Be Held in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 30 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of
African Unity (OAU) announced Friday that the OAU Ministerial
Meeting on Refugees, Returnees and Displaced Persons will be held
in Sudan from December 10 to 15.
</P>
<P>
A press release issued here by the OAU said, an agreement for
hosting the meeting in Sudan was signed Friday at the OAU General
Secretariat.
</P>
<P>
Signing on behalf of the OAU, Acting Secretary General Daniel
Antonio said the pan-African organization will do whatever it can
to make the meeting a success. He also thanked the government of
Sudan for creating a favourable atmosphere to host the
conference.
</P>
<P>
El Karib, Charge d'Affaires in the Sudanese Embassy to
Ethiopia who signed on behalf his government, commended the OAU
for its support so far, saying that he hoped the conference will
be successful.
</P>
<P>
Sudan proposed to host the meeting at the 66th Ordinary
Session of the OAU Council of Ministers in Harare in 1997, and
the invitation was then accepted and reconfirmed in Ouagadougou,
Burkina Faso, last June.
</P>
<P>
According to the OAU, There are about seven million refugees
and about 20 million internally displaced people in Africa.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is aimed at finding a durable solution to the
problem of refugees, returnees and the displaced in Africa, the
press release added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
