<HEADLINE> Tanzania Gets $51 Million as Cotton Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 30 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania has earned 51
million U.S. Dollars from exporting 36,200 tons of cotton lint by
the end of September as the 1998/99 cotton buying season is in
full swing.
</P>
<P>
The east African state got 91.4 million Dollars from exports
of 60,938 tons of cotton lint during the 1997/98 buying season,
usually from July to October, newspapers here said Friday.
</P>
<P>
They quoted an official of the Tanzania Cotton Lint and Seed
Board as saying that from the 1994/95 season to present, the
country has earned a total of 392.6 million Dollars from
exporting a total of 259,763 tons of cotton lint.
</P>
<P>
Known as "white gold" for its clear white color, Tanzania's
cotton lint, mainly produced in the western regions of Shinyanga,
Mwanza and Mara, is exported mainly to Indonesia, Malaysia,
Italy, South Africa and Portugal as well as Taiwan. 
