<HEADLINE> Pinochet Wins Symbolic Bail in Britain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 30 (Xinhua) -- Former Chilean president Augusto
Pinochet was granted conditional bail by the British High Court in
London Friday.
</P>
<P>
However, Judge Stephen Richards agreed to the bail plea only on
two conditions -- that Pinochet reside "at all times" in London's
Grovelands hospital and that he be "guarded by police at all
times".
</P>
<P>
Pinochet, who was arrested by British police on alleged
involvement in genocide and torture of Spanish citizens early this
month, won a major legal battle Wednesday when the High Court said
his former status as head of state gave him immunity from
prosecution.
</P>
<P>
Early this week, Pinochet was moved from the London Clinic,
where he had his back operation, to the Grovelands Priory
Hospital, an exclusive psychiatric clinic.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a Chilean air force jet is waiting at an airport in
Oxfordshire, central England, ready to whisk Pinochet away should
he be freed by the courts. 
</P>
