<HEADLINE> Jubilee 2000 Debt Campaign Launched in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, October 30 (Xinhua) -- Jubilee 2000, a worldwide
campaign for total cancellation of the unpayable of external debt
of poor countries has been officially launched here Friday
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Spearheaded by the Uganda Debt Network (UDN), a coalition of
non-governmental organizations, individuals and institutions, the
campaign is aimed at ensuring that poor people can have a
debt-free start in the next millennium.
</P>
<P>
A UDN report says the third world countries owe over 2.2
trillion U.S. Dollars to international creditors. Sub-Sahara
Africa owes over 235 billion Dollars while the external debt of
Uganda alone reaches over 3.6 billion Dollars to the
international community.
</P>
<P>
The UDN was formed in 1996 when the external debt burden of
third world countries and its adverse impact on social and
economic development became a critical issue of concern.
</P>
<P>
Figures of UDN show that in 1980 Uganda's debt stock stood at
689 million Dollars. Over 76 percent of Uganda's debt is owed to
the World Bank and the International Monetary Fund.
</P>
<P>
Uganda pays over 140 million Dollars in debt service annually.
Every child, woman, man owes over nine Dollars in debt service
per person while it spends only 3.95 Dollars on health per
person.
</P>
<P>
The Jubilee 2000 Global Campaign is a worldwide movement that
was launched in 1996 in the United Kingdom by a group of
church-related organizations, trade unions, civic groups,
academicians and research institutions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981031.0039 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Debt Is Major Obstacle to Development: Ugandan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, October 30 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan First Lady Janet
Museveni said Friday that the massive external debt constitutes
the major obstacle to the sustainable economic development of
poor countries.
</P>
<P>
The first lady made the remarks when launching the Jubilee
2000 Debt Campaign here Friday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The most painful thing with the external debt burden is the
fact that it mostly affects children because they grow up stunted
and eventually fail to attain education.
</P>
<P>
Janet said globally, environmental degradation has escalated
as poor people try to cope with the harsh conditions of the
economy.
</P>
<P>
Some countries are blamed for failure to use the borrowed
money wisely. She called on third world countries to exhibit
maturity in the way they manage their affairs to inspire
confidence in their lenders and the international community as a
whole.
</P>
<P>
She told the conference that Uganda has already embarked on
this new road and that the money saved from the debt relief
initiative amounting to 650 million U.S. Dollars has been put to
alleviate poverty in the country.
</P>
<P>
According to a report here, each year the third world pays the
West three times more in debt repayments than it receives in aid.
</P>
<P>
Of the 32 countries classified as Highly Indebted Poor
Countries, 25 are in sub-Sahara Africa. The huge debt is a
staggering burden for poor but developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
