<HEADLINE> Angola Sees 400,000 More Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, October 30 (Xinhua) -- Angola has seen 400,000 more
refugees due to the unstable military situations in the
past seven months, a senior official said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Albino Malunge, Minister of Social Welfare and Assistance,
made the remarks during his meeting with visiting chairman of
Namibian National Committee (parliament) Kandy Nehiva.
</P>
<P>
Many civilians have fled their homes since March when the
peace process hit snags and more reported raids on common people
were mounted by the fighters of the National Union for Total
Independence of Angola (UNITA), Malunge said.
</P>
<P>
There are still one million internally displaced people
waiting to be settled in the country, with the hardest hit area
being the Malanje Province in the northwest, he said.
</P>
<P>
Eighty percent of the emergency fund from the international
community has been used for refugees settlement, leaving little
for development, the minister noted.
</P>
<P>
For this, he said, the government has suspended its efforts to
repatriate the refugees abroad, since 34,000 out of the 120,000
refugees having returned to Angola are waiting to be settled.
</P>
<P>
There are still tens of thousands of Angolan refugees in
Namibia, said Malunge, who hoped that the Namibian government
could understand this situation and continue to take care of the
displaced Angolans.
</P>
<P>
Nehiva arrived in Luanda last Saturday for a week-long visit.
</P>
</TEXT>
