<HEADLINE> China: Globalization Should be Put Back on Right Track </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 30 (Xinhua) -- The globalization and
liberalization should be put back on the right track so that all
countries could enjoy real and equal benefit from the process,
China stressed here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the 53rd session of the General Assembly, Chinese
delegate Yuan Shaofu said globalization did not mean
uniformization, and every country had the right in light of its
characteristics to choose its own way of participating in
globalization.
</P>
<P>
Yuan Shaofu said liberalization was not an end in itself but a
means to the real goal of promoting development and eliminate
poverty.
</P>
<P>
Yuan said Liberalization in any sector must take account of the
specific conditions, levels of development and sustaining capacity
of the country concerned, and liberalization in service sectors
such as finance should take into consideration the developing
countries' special difficulties, respect their policy goals and
readiness to join the process.
</P>
<P>
The delegate said the developed countries should
comprehensively and faithfully fulfill the commitments they made
in the Uruguay Round Agreements by eliminating all tariff and
non-tariff barriers so as to provide greater market access to
developing countries' competitive products.  
</P>
</TEXT>
