<HEADLINE> Gomez Moves to Finals in Singles, Doubles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, October 31 (Xinhua)-- Andres Gomez of Ecuador advanced
to finals in both singles and doubles after he won Saturday's
semifinals in both events of the NTT Data Championships senior
tennis tournament.
</P>
<P>
Gomez beat American Tim Wilkisson 6-4, 6-2 to set up a final
on Sunday with Jimmy Connors, the No. 1 seed and defending
champion.
</P>
<P>
Connors, former No. 1 in the world, defeated fellow American
Mel Purcell 6-3, 6-1 in Saturday's another semifinal.
</P>
<P>
In doubles, Gomez paired with Purcell to edged Yannick Noah of
France and Wilkisson 6-4, 7-6 (7-5).
</P>
<P>
In day's another doubles, Mansour Bahrami of France and Peter
Flemming of the United States trounced Henri Leconte of France
and Bjorn Borg of Sweden 4-6, 6-1, 10-5. The last set was a
champions tie-breaker.
</P>
<P>
The NTT Data Champions is the 16th event on the 1998 World
Senior Tennis Circuit. The tour includes the Nuveen Tour in the
United States, the ATP Senior Tour of Champions in Europe and the
Champions Tour in the rest of the world.  
</P>
