unanimously that Spain has the legal right to bring criminal
charges against Chile's former dictator, General Augusto Pinochet,
and to seek his extradition from Britain. The judges' decision,
which is based on a large body of international humanitarian law,
contradicted a ruling by the High Court in London, which said that
Britain had no authority to arrest the general.
</P>
