</P>
<P>
-- The U.S. economy grew at an unexpectedly strong pace in the
July-to-September period, the Commerce Department said Friday,
despite turmoil in global financial markets. The 3.3 percent
annual rate reported by the department was a full percentage point
or more higher than many analysts had expected.
</P>
<P>
-- The United Nations Security Council agreed Friday on the
nature and scope of a comprehensive review of Iraq's relations
with the United Nations that the council has offered to undertake
if Baghdad complies with its orders and resumes cooperation with
U.N. weapons inspectors. 
