<DOCNO> XIE19981031.0079 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Int'l Conference on Moral Values Ends in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 31 (Xinhua) -- The three-day international
conference under the theme of "spiritual and moral values for a
better 21st century" concluded here Saturday with the unanimous
adoption of the Kathmandu Declaration.
</P>
<P>
The main goal of the conference attended by over 2,000
participants from 38 countries all over the world was the
betterment of society through the upliftment and fulfillment of
the individual at a time when humanity has made astounding
progress in the material field but is troubled by numerous complex
problems because of crisis of values.
</P>
<P>
The declaration noted that the methods proposed were
restoration of the intrinsic goodness of humankind and creation of
an environment of freedom from all types of exploitation --
social, religious and economic -- through the understanding and
application of spiritual principles.
</P>
<P>
Four plenary sessions as well as seminars were held during the
conference with the focus on the role of professionals including
doctors, jurists and educators.
</P>
<P>
"The speakers highlighted the ill health, lawlessness,
indiscipline and lack of purpose engendered by over-emphasis on
material values," the declaration said.
</P>
<P>
With this in mind, the Brahma Kumaris Rajyoga Center in Nepal,
the organizer of the conference, invited the participants to
commit themselves to act in accordance with the following
four-point plan, the declaration noted.
</P>
<P>
1. Reflection -- take a minimum of three minutes each day to
look within the self, identify a positive quality such as peace,
love, or a sense of service and resolve to increase it in action;
</P>
<P>
2. Connection -- maintain spiritual power by fostering an
attitude of being an instrument for a higher purpose;
</P>
<P>
3. Application -- develop spiritual and moral values by
purposefully choosing to see them at work in ourselves and in
others;
</P>
<P>
4. Service -- promote renewal of the highest human values by
sharing spiritual understanding with others and supporting those
engaged in this task.
</P>
<P>
The Brahma Kumaris Rajyoga Centre of Nepal is a
non-governmental organization working in the filed of value and
meditation education.
</P>
<P>
There are over 4,700 such centers spread over as many as 72
countries with the international headquarters based in Mount Abu,
India. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
