<HEADLINE> Over 30,000 Ethiopians Repatriated from Eritrea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 31 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia's National Fund
Soliciting Committee announced on Saturday that the number of
Ethiopians repatriated from Eritrea has reached over 30,000.
</P>
<P>
The committee was quoted by the Ethiopian News Agency as
saying that 12,763 of them returned home via different zones of
northern Tigray State, 17,417 via Bure and 66 through Djibouti.
</P>
<P>
The committee said efforts have been made to permanently
rehabilitate the deportees.
</P>
<P>
The committee also said some 188,690 Ethiopians, without
including those repatriated from Eritrea, have been displaced by
the border dispute between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The committee called on Ethiopians and the international
community to continue with their assistance to the displaced
whose number, it said, is increasing from time to time.
</P>
<P>
Heads of States from Burkina Faso, Zimbabwe and Djibouti as
well as leaders of Ethiopia and Eritrea have agreed to hold a
two-day summit on November 7 and 8 in Ouagadougou to help resolve
the Territorial dispute between the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
