<HEADLINE> Reconstruction Work on Beijing's Tiananmen Square Begins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 31 (Xinhua) -- A seven-month reconstruction
project on Tiananmen Square started today.
</P>
<P>
Entries to the square have been closed and no tourists can be
seen on it. More than 800 construction workers are setting up
fences on all sides of the square, but the flag-raising ceremony
stays and can be seen from Changan Avenue.
</P>
<P>
The project involves improvements to the pavement and the
weather-beaten and worn-out public address and lighting systems on
the world's largest square.
</P>
<P>
The bricks on the square will be replaced with granite, the
public-address system modernized, the low-wattage road lights
replaced with more efficient lights, and more decorative lights
will be used to illuminate the buildings around the square. The
fountains on the Jinshui Moat will also be improved.
</P>
<P>
The project is expected to be completed by the end of next May,
official said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
