<HEADLINE> Over 500 Taken Ill by Chlorine Gas Leakage in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 31 (Xinhua) -- Over 500 people were taken
ill on inhaling chlorine gas which leaked from cylinders after a
truck carrying them overturned in northwest India, the Press Trust
of India (PTI) reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The truck overturned Friday night near Bhoyan Ghati, a southern
village of Rajasthan state, causing leakage of gas which spread to
a dozen nearby villages, said PTI.
</P>
<P>
About 550 people, two of them seriously ill, were reportedly
taken to a local primary health center for treatment.
</P>
<P>
Villagers complained of burning sensation in their eyes and
chest after inhaling the gas.
</P>
<P>
PTI said that atmosphere in and around the spot where the
accident occurred later cleared and the traffic on the road was
resumed. 
</P>
