<HEADLINE> Roundup: Congressional Contacts Tightens Sino-Russian Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 31 (Xinhua) -- Frequent high-level contacts
between the highest law-making bodies of China and Russia have
actively helped promote bilateral congressional ties and the
development of a Sino-Russian strategic partnership.
</P>
<P>
The latest and most important was the one made by Gennady
Seleznev, chairman of the Russian Duma, the parliament of the
country.
</P>
<P>
Seleznev paid an official visit to China between October 25 and
30 at the invitation of Li Peng, chairman of China's National
People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, and Li Ruihuan, the chairman of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference National
Committee, all met with Seleznev.
</P>
<P>
During these high-level meetings, the two sides agreed that
contacts between the congresses are an important part of the
Sino-Russian strategic partnership, increasing understanding,
expanding contacts and consolidating friendship.
</P>
<P>
The two sides expressed satisfaction with cooperation in
various fields in recent years, and congressional leaders also say
that they should help increase trade and regional exchanges.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also agreed that there is big potential in
economic cooperation as the economies of China and Russia are
complementary. However, the cooperation has not yet reached the
level it should have done.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that Sino-Russian trade in the first nine
months of the year amounted to 4.1 billion U.S. dollars, 2.7
percent less than a year earlier. More efforts should be made to
speed up cooperation.
</P>
<P>
To this end, the two sides stressed the two countries should
promote mutual understanding, strengthen cooperation in planned
and other projects, and develop relations between localities,
particularly trade and economic contacts at the border areas.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also pledged to encourage mutual investment for
establishing joint-venture enterprises in both countries.
</P>
<P>
It is convinced that increasing exchanges between congresses
will continue to give an impetus to bilateral cooperation in
various fields and play a positive role in the further development
of Sino-Russian relations.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
