<HEADLINE> Air Portugal Ends Macao-Lisbon Flight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 31 (Xinhua) -- Beginning from November, there
will be no through flight linking Macao with European cities now
that Air Portugal is scheduled to end its flights to Macao on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
A plane serving the last Lisbon-Macao flight is scheduled to
land at the Macao Airport at 4:50 Saturday afternoon. Then the
airplane will leave for Lisbon at 6:45 Saturday evening.
</P>
<P>
Air Portugal started the Macao-Lisbon air route on April 1,
1996. Some time later, however, the flight had to stop in Bangkok
and pick up more passengers.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the airline said the ending of the air route is
due to heavy losses. 
</P>
