<HEADLINE> Taiwanese Murderer Jailed for Life in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hanoi, 0ctober 31 (Xinhua) -- A life imprisonment sentence was
handed down to a Taiwanese murderer Hou Ming Chin by the Ho Chi
Minh city people's court on Thursday, according to Vietnam News
Agency Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Hou, born in 1956, was convicted of murder.
</P>
<P>
The report said the Taiwanese started his business at the
Bochen Wood Export Company in Vietnam's southern province of Dong
Nai in 1992. Later he withdrew his investment from the company but
returned to Vietnam many times since.
</P>
<P>
The accused, together with three other Taiwanese organized the
killing of Wu Wen Yu and Chang Po Wen, also Taiwanese, on June 27,
1997, because of a financial disagreement.
</P>
<P>
Hou was arrested while he was clearing custom procedures on his
way to Cambodia. Vietnamese police have issued search warrants for
the three remaining criminals. 
</P>
