<HEADLINE> Vietnam Posts Solid Growth in Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 31 (Xinhua) -- Agriculture has side-stepped the
regional economic crisis to post solid growth around Vietnam, the
official Vietnam News Agency (VNA) reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Food yields have increased by 700,000 tons over last year, with
cattle and poultry figures rising sharply, VNA quoted the General
Department of Statistics as saying.
</P>
<P>
The country now boasts three million buffalo, four million
cattle and 18 million pigs, up 0.5 percent, 2.2 percent and 2.3
percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Higher food yields mean a greater supply of animal fodder at a
lower price, and livestock farmers have responded.
</P>
<P>
Information on livestock rearing techniques has allowed many
farmers to gear their efforts towards commodity markets.
</P>
<P>
In the southern provinces commodity-oriented livestock rearing
has been popular for many years, and animal herds have grown
rapidly.
</P>
<P>
This year pig herds have increased by 3.2 percent and cattle by
two percent.
</P>
<P>
Even more effort has been poured into the processing industry,
ensuring that the size and quality of livestock around the country
continues to grow, VNA said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
