<HEADLINE> Vietnam Takes Measures to Develop Farm Processing Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 31 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam is taking measures to
develop agricultural produce processing industry in order to
promote farm produce export, Vietnam News Agency reported
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's agriculture sector has mapped out measures to
mobilize all sources of capital to develop the farm-forestry
produce processing industry.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's agriculture sector will give priority to key
industries making highly competitive products for export.
Attention will be paid to developing small-scale processing
establishments in rural areas and setting up joint-ventures in
various forms between farmers, cooperatives and processing
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam is now one of the world leading exporters of rice, with
millions of tons of rice being sold abroad every year.
</P>
<P>
Rice processing is one of the most developed processing
industries in the country.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's agricultural sector plans to build more storage and
processing facilities for the export-rice zones to ensure between
4-4.5 million tons of rice for export a year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
