<DOCNO> XIE19981031.0129 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xiamen Customs Introduces New Declaration System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, October 31 (Xinhua) -- Xiamen Customs in east China's
Fujian Province recently introduced a new declaration system to
improve supervision over export goods.
</P>
<P>
The new system requires seagoing shipments of export cargo to
arrive at designated docks or storage yards 24 hours in advance of
declaration.
</P>
<P>
The fact that shippers can complete five clearance procedures in
the joint inspection center will raise efficiency and eliminate
loopholes in customs inspections.
</P>
<P>
Xiamen Customs is first to adopt the system. The city, one of
China's five special economic zones, has been one of the areas to
experiment with various reform measures.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
