<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Killed, 32 Injured in Bomb Blast in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 31 (Xinhua) -- Two people were killed and 32
others injured Saturday morning in a bomb blast in Pakistan's
Punjab province.
</P>
<P>
The explosion took place at 8:55 a.m. in Sialkot, about 150
kilometers north of the provincial capital of Lahore, according to
a report by the Associated Press of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The bomb weighing five pounds had been planted in an abandoned
bicycle parked along the iron fence of a bridge, said the report.
</P>
<P>
It said that the injured were rushed to a nearby hospital where
all the doctors have been summoned on emergency basis to provide
treatment to them.
</P>
<P>
The condition of seven of the injured is stated to be critical,
the report said. 
</P>
