<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chairman Mao Memorial Hall Closes Temporarily </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 31 (Xinhua) -- The Chairman Mao Memorial Hall
will be closed between November 2 this year and March 15 of next
year, to facilitate renovation of the yard of the hall and the
Tiananmen Square.
</P>
<P>
The announcement came from the hall's administration today.
</P>
<P>
Yesterday, the Beijing Municipal government
announced that a seven-month reconstruction project on
Tiananmen Square has started.
</P>
<P>
The reconstruction will involve improvements to the pavement
and the weather-beaten and worn-out public address and lighting
systems on the world's largest square, which will be closed for
that period of time.
</P>
<P>
The bricks on the square will be replaced with granite, the
public-address system modernized, the low-wattage road lights
replaced with more efficient lights, and more decorative lights
will be used to illuminate the buildings around the square. The
fountains on the Jinshui Moat will also be improved.
</P>
<P>
The flag-hoisting ceremony will, however, be continued and can
be seen from the Changan Avenue, that separates the Tiananmen
Rostrum and the square. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
