<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Simplified Entry Procedures Rendered to Taiwan Business People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 31 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Public Security
has decided to allow simpler entry and exit procedures and longer
stays in Chinese mainland for Taiwan business people with large
and sound investment on the mainland, today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
Under new policies, Taiwan investors with big investment on the
mainland for more than five years and with good economic returns
can now have their valid Taiwan Citizen Entry and Exit Passport
for the mainland stamped for unlimited comings and goings as well
as temporary residence of up to five years.
</P>
<P>
As for how much investment can be called "big" and how much
earnings "good", the ministry said that will depend upon
comparisons with other Taiwan-founded enterprises in the same
field.
</P>
<P>
The policy is also valid for qualifying enterprises' high-level
managers. The maximum length of stay for the main technical and
managerial staff of such enterprises, their spouses and children
is three years.
</P>
<P>
The maximum stay for managers of other Taiwan-funded companies,
their spouses and children, and Taiwan people permitted by the
ministry to work in the mainland is now two years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
