<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rongchang Pig Becomes Internationally Renowned </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, October 31 (Xinhua) -- The Rongchang Pig from
Chongqing Municipality has been cited as one of the eight brand
name pigs of the world.
</P>
<P>
The pig is said to have been brought by immigrants from Hunan
Province in central China to Rongchang County in southwest China
400 years ago where it has been nurtured as a fine-quality variety
through the years.
</P>
<P>
After it was selected one of the three Chinese brand names in
the 1980s, the species has been further improved by means of
modern technology. Capable of being raised in both plateau and
plain areas and in various climates, it has become the most widely
raised pig in China. Except for Taiwan, all regions of china are
now raising the breed.
</P>
<P>
China raises four billion pigs a year, making it the largest
pig-raising country in the world. Rongchang County alone produces
over 1.8 million pigs a year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
