<HEADLINE> Philippine Boxing Team Hopes to Sweep Asian Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Coach Boy Catolico said here Friday that "winning all the
seven gold medals is a difficult assignment, but we will try to
win all the gold medals at stake."
</P>
<P>
Amateur Boxing Association of the Philippines (ABAP) president
Mannny Lopez said the boxing team will be spear-headed by World
Championships' first Filipino silver medalist light-flyweight
Ronel Velasco, who is also a bronze medalist of the 1992
Barcelona Olympic Games and of the 1998 New York Goodwill Games.
</P>
<P>
Other named for the team were light-flyweight Arian Lerin,
bantamweight Rico Morano, featherweight Eric Camy, lightweight
Joel Barriga, 1994 Asian Games light-welterweight gold medalist
Revnaldo Galido and welterweight Romeo Brin.
</P>
<P>
The team will leave on November 6 for Cuba where they will
undergo rigid training under the supervision of Cuban coach Raul
Fernandez Liranza, the same coach who helped Mananeto Velasco Jr.
win the country's only second silver medal in the 1996 Atlanta
Olympics.
</P>
<P>
From Cuba, the team will proceed straight to Bangkok on
December 6.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines won three gold medals in boxing in the 1994
Asian Games in Hiroshima, Japan. 
</P>
