<HEADLINE> DPRK Leader Meets Hyundai Honorary President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, October 31 (Xinhua) -- Kim Jong Il, leader of the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK), met Chung Ju-Yung,
honorary president of South Korea's Hyundai Group, here Friday,
the local press reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
In his first meeting with a visitor this year, Kim welcomed
Chung's five-day visit here, the second in four months, the
reports said.
</P>
<P>
Kim had conversations with Chung and his family "in an amicable
atmosphere," the reports said.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Chung's entourage discussed with DPRK
officials on the development of tourism in Mount Kumgangsan and
Hyundai Group's other non-governmental cooperation projects with
the DPRK.
</P>
<P>
Chung arrived here Tuesday through Panmunjom and will return to
Seoul by the same way Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Political observers believe that this is a sign of easing
tensions between the DPRK and South Korea and is expected to
promote the peace process in the Korean Peninsula. 
</P>
