<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Troops Kill 30 Rebels, Destroys 7 Boats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 31 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan Navy Friday killed
30 Tamil rebels and destroyed seven boats in a battle off
Mullaitivu sea in the northeast of the country, according to
military sources Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The sources said seven rebel boats were destroyed and 30 rebels
killed when a convoy of nine attack craft of the Sri Lanka Navy
providing protection to MV Lanka Mudhitha confronted them off
Mullaitivu sea, about 300 kilometers from Colombo.
</P>
<P>
The MV Lanka Mudhitha was transporting civilians and soldiers
from Kankesanturai to Trincomalee when the convoy of 15 Tiger
boats surrounded the navy boats, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The sources added that two of navy attack craft were slightly
damaged in the attack.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting against the government
since 1983 for an independent homeland for minority Tamils in the
north and east of the country. 
</P>
