<DOCNO> XIE19981031.0160 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Belarus FM Opposes NATO's Eastward Expansion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MINSK, October 30 (Xinhua) -- Belarus is opposed to the North
Atlantic Treaty Organization's (NATO) eastward expansion since it
threatens the country's national security and interests,
Belarussian Foreign Minister Ivan Antonovich said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, Antonovich said NATO's decision to
move eastward is a mistake on grounds that the Warsaw Treaty
Organization has fallen apart and the threat of a military
invasion against NATO countries no longer exists.
</P>
<P>
If NATO moves eastward to the Belarussian border, Antonovich
said, Belarus will be in direct confrontation with NATO, which is
a threat to the country's national interests and security.
</P>
<P>
Belarus will never allow the Belarus-Poland borders to become a
new dividing line on the Europe continent, Antonovich said.
</P>
<P>
He called on NATO to shift its focus from military to political
tasks, and said his country is willing to conduct dialogue with a
reformed NATO and help prevent the occurrence of a new dividing
line in Europe.
</P>
<P>
On the Kosovo issue, Antonovich reiterated Belarus' opposition
to any NATO military strike against the Yugoslav Federation.
</P>
<P>
He said his country has repeatedly urged NATO to abandon
military plans, and believes the only way to end the Kosovo crisis
is that all parties concerned comply with relevant UN Security
Council resolutions.
</P>
<P>
Military strikes will lead nowhere but fuel the confrontation
in Kosovo, he said, warning that NATO's military attacks may
trigger another round of large-scale military clashes in Kosovo.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981031.0161 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-31 </DATE_TIME>
