<HEADLINE> Southern Common Market Members to Hold Military Maneuver </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, October 30 (Xinhua) -- The four member countries of
the Southern Common Market (Mercosur) will hold a military
exercise in Argentina from November 2 to 7.
</P>
<P>
Col. Osorio Ferraz Gominho, spokesman for Brazilian Southern
Military Command, made the announcement on Friday in Porto Alegre,
capital of the Rio Grande do Sul state.
</P>
<P>
He said the military of Brazil, Argentina, Uruguay and Paraguay
will take part in the exercise, the third of Mercosur countries.
</P>
<P>
Ferraz Gominho said that this exercise will simulate a
U.N. peace mission and will be held in the Argentine city of Paso
de los Libres, across the border from the city of Uruguaima, in
the Rio Grande do Sul state of Brazil.
</P>
<P>
The first joint Mercosur military exercise was held in 1996 in
Argentina with the participation of the Brazilian and Argentine
troops.
</P>
<P>
The second was held last year in Rosario do Sul in Brazil with
the participation of 2,300 troops from Brazil, Argentina, and
Uruguay. 
</P>
</TEXT>
