<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Bank Indonesia has again lowered interest rates of
guaranteed time-deposit, the Bisnis Indonesia reported
Saturday. (Indonesia-Interest Rate)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LIMA -- Peruvian total exports accounted to only more than four
billion U.S. dollars during the first nine months of this year, a
22.79 percent drop against the same period of 1997. (Peru-Exports)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CARACAS -- The price for the Venezuelan crude closed the week
at 10.99 U.S. dollars a barrel, 0.40 dollars above the close of
last week, the Mines and Energy Ministry said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
This rise in the average price puts the October average at
11.14 dollars, more than the 11.10 dollar average for the year,
but far below the 15.50 dollars estimated by the government for
1998, and under the 16.32 registered in 1997. (Venezuela-Oil-Price)
</P>
