BRASILIA -- Two Brazilian large state-owned energy enterprises
will reduce their budgets by 1.8 billion reals (1.512 billion
U.S. dollars) under a government's fiscal adjustment, a senior
official said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The budget cut for Petrobras will be 980 million dollars, and
532 million dollars in Electrobras, Mines and Energy Minister
Raimundo Britto said. (Brazil-State Firms-Budget)
</P>
<P>
