<HEADLINE> New Annex of Myanmar Daewoo Garment Factory Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, October 31 (Xinhua) -- A new annex to the garment
factory of Myanmar Daewoo International Ltd. opened here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar Daewoo International Ltd., jointly established by the
Union of Myanmar Economic Holdings Ltd. and Daewoo Corporation of
the Republic of Korea, was formed on January 23, 1991, and the
factory began to operate on September 25 the same year.
</P>
<P>
Previously, it produced 490,000 dozens of garments annually,
and with the new annex, it can produce 600,000 dozens of garments.
</P>
<P>
The factory produces and exports shirts, blouses and pajamas,
and as they suit the tastes of countries which import, demand is
on the increase.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar Daewoo International Ltd. began with 700 employees, and
the number of employees has increased to over 2,700 who produce
24,000 items of clothing per day.
</P>
<P>
Daewoo Corporation has established nine joint ventures in
Myanmar with 8,000 Myanmar employees.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, the Republic of Korea's
investment in Myanmar reached at 99.33 million U.S. dollars in 20
projects up to the end of March this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
