<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bank Indonesia Lowers Interest Rates Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 31 (Xinhua) -- Bank Indonesia has again
lowered interest rates of guaranteed time-deposit, the Bisnis
Indonesia reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
This is the fifth time in five weeks the central bank lowered
its interest rate.
</P>
<P>
The rate for one-month deposit is now 59 percent, down from the
previous 61 percent, for next week (November 2 to 8), said Perry
Warjiyo of the central bank.
</P>
<P>
He said that the rate for next week's guaranteed three-month
deposit is set at 58 percent, down from the previous 60 percent.
</P>
<P>
Rates for next week's guaranteed six-month and 12-month
deposits are set at 48 percent and 46 percent respectively, down
one percent from the previous week.
</P>
<P>
Bank Indonesia also set the U.S.-dollar denominated deposit
interest rate at 15 percent for 1, 3 and 12 months period, while
the 24-month deposit interest rate remains at 18 percent.
</P>
<P>
The guaranteed inter-bank call money is set at 45 percent, down
from the previous 53 percent, while the U.S. dollar-denominated
inter-bank call money is set at 13 percent, up from the previous
11 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
