<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Six Killed in Domino Bump In First Fall Fog </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, October 31 (Xinhua) -- Eighty-two vehicles had
domino-fashion collisions friday morning, causing six deaths on
site and a couple of others injuried at an expressway in East
China's Anhui province.
</P>
<P>
The tragic traffic accident occured in the region's first fall
heavy fog on the expressway linking Hefei and Nanjing cities,
provincial capitals of East China's Anhui and Jiangsu Provinces
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The first two trucks' bump was reported at 5:20 yesterday
morning. In about two and a half hours, 80 vehicles, the majority
of them overloaded trucks, had head-to-tail collisions on a
stretch of less than three kilometers in the direction from
Nanjing to Hefei.
</P>
<P>
No accidents occurred on the other direction of the highway.
</P>
<P>
The vehicles bumped into each other in groups. Some even landed
on the partition fence. The majority of the vehicles suffered
severe damages, with more than ten reduced to sheer scraps.
</P>
<P>
The wreckage was cleared off the road by 11:00 am before the
traffic resumed normal flow.
</P>
<P>
The injured people, the number of which is yet to be released,
are now safe after immediate medical care in hospital, said Zhang
Hui, deputy director of the Anhui Province High Grade Highway
Administration.
</P>
<P>
Zhang attributed the tragedy mainly to the heavy foggy weather,
adding that drivers tended to feel very tired and loosen their
guard after a whole night's driving.
</P>
<P>
The majority of trucks were overloaded causing braking systems
to be slow and ineffective, which also contributed to the traffic
accident, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
