<HEADLINE> Peruvian Exports Drop Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, October 30 (Xinhua) -- Peruvian total exports accounted
to only more than four billion U.S. dollars during the first nine
months of this year, a 22.79 percent drop against the same period
of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Last year's exports from January to September were 5.2 billion
U.S. dollars, according to the Exporters Promotion Commission
(Promex).
</P>
<P>
The commission said on Friday that the exports of traditional
products fell by 31.68 percent.
</P>
<P>
These products exports amounted to 2.53 billion dollars between
January and September of this year in comparison with 3.7 billion
dollars of last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
