<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Expressway Under Construction in China's Largest Bonded Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, October 31 (Xinhua) -- Construction of a
25.93-kilometer-long expressway linking the Yangpu Development
Zone and the western expressway of Hainan Island began recently.
</P>
<P>
The 240-million-yuan (28.915 million U.S. dollars) road project
marks a new round of construction in the development zone, the
largest bonded zone in China, local sources said.
</P>
<P>
Since construction of the development zone covering over 30
square kilometers began five years ago, over five billion yuan
has been put into infrastructure, including a power
plant, roads, housing and telecommunication facilities.
</P>
<P>
Also, an expressway built by the Hainan provincial government
at a cost of 2.2 billion yuan is already open to traffic. The
second phase of the Yangpu Port, built by the central government
with 780 million yuan, is now under construction, and a
310-million-yuan water supply project will start construction soon.
</P>
<P>
This year has seen the start of three infrastructure projects
and eight industrial projects with investment totaling over five
billion yuan in the zone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
