<DOCNO> XIE19981031.0180 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Suspends Import of Sub-standard Medicine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 31 (Xinhua) -- China has suspended the import
of 21 medicines after they twice failed to reach the required
standards during quality inspections at Chinese customs, reported
China Daily today.
</P>
<P>
Zheng Xiaoyu, administrator of the State Drug Administration
(SDA) explained that import will be stopped immediately if two
batches of substandard foreign medicines are found, said the paper.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time the SDA has released the results of
medicine quality inspection since it was established two months
ago.
</P>
<P>
"The prime responsibility of the SDA is to crack down on the
manufacture and sale of fake and sub-standard medicines and ensure
the safety and effectiveness of medicine for the public," Zheng
was quoted as saying.  
</P>
