<HEADLINE> Increasing Flood Control Capacity In Eastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, October 31 (Xinhua) -- Most parts of the province of
Jiangxi that were hit by this summer's severe flooding have worked
out plans for improving flood controls, with government funding.
</P>
<P>
Jiangxi was one of the worst-hit areas on the Yangtze River and
surrounding lakes in the summer. The central government has
already allocated 490 million yuan (59 million U.S. dollars) for
building new towns for resettling people, local sources say.
</P>
<P>
The plan is to expand Jiangxi's flood diversion area by 1,306
square kilometers and storage area by 6.8 billion cubic meters by
dismantaling protective embankments and turning reclaimed land
back into river beds and lakes.
</P>
<P>
The plan will affect 467,500 people who have been living on the
reclaimed land. The province will build 37 new townships, 150
central villages, and over 400 basic villages for them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
