<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Oil Price Closes Week at 10.99 U.S. Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, October 30 (Xinhua) -- The price for the Venezuelan
crude closed the week at 10.99 U.S. dollars a barrel, 0.40 dollars
above the close of last week, the Mines and Energy Ministry said
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
This rise in the average price puts the October average at
11.14 dollars, more than the 11.10 dollar average for the year,
but far below the 15.50 dollars estimated by the government for
1998, and under the 16.32 registered in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Official spokesmen attributed the oil market weakness to the
excess supply and to the existence of enormous inventories
accumulated by the main consumers.
</P>
<P>
Oil accounts for 70 percent of Venezuelan exports and provides
more than 50 percent of the income for its national budget.
</P>
<P>
The Venezuelan treasury misses some 1.2 billion U.S. dollars a
year for every dollar the crude oil barrel price drops, said
official sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
