<HEADLINE> Arms Smuggling Group Caught in Switzerland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, October 30 (Xinhua) -- The Swiss police arrested
members of an arms smuggling group this week and confiscated a
large amount of weapons, ammunition and cash, the local press
reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The group, which involved six people, is suspected of selling
weapons to Kosovo. Four of the six are Yugoslavians, one Swiss and
one Arabian.
</P>
<P>
The suspects were apprehended while discussing a
multi-million-dollar deal to smuggle more weapons to Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
In a search of their residences, the police confiscated 1,000
kilograms of ammunition, a large cache of weapons and 230,000
Swiss francs (170,000 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
A Swiss police officer involved in the case said the two
railway containers loaded with weapons destined for Kosovo are in
the custody of Albania's Custom Office. 
</P>
