<HEADLINE> U.S. Stocks Extend Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, October 30 (Xinhua) -- U.S. stocks rebounded
strongly on Friday, driven by encouraging new economic data.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average jumped 97.07 points or 1.1
percent to close at 8592.10, retreating from a gain of nearly 175
points because of profit-taking.
</P>
<P>
The rally, following a 123 point surge in the previous session,
made the blue-chip index advancing 139 points for the week and 749
points for October, or 9.6 percent gain for the month.
</P>
<P>
The Commerce Department reported on Friday that the U.S. economy
grew 3.3 percent in the third quarter, up from 1.8 percent in the
previous quarter.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile the group of seven major industrialized nations
Friday unveiled a package of far-reaching reforms designed to
strengthen the global financial system, which soothed worries in
the market here about worldwide recession.
</P>
<P>
On the New York Stock Exchange, advancers beat decliners 5-2
with trading volume up to 784 million shares from 695 million
previously.
</P>
<P>
In other trading, the Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index rose 12.74 to
1098.67, the technology-linked Nasdaq composite index rose 14.20
1771.39.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE composite index rose 7.04 to 543.35 and the American
Stock Exchange composite index rose 7.93 to 645.41.  
